Button.applyDamageTitle: Assign the Damage to the Targets!
Button.applyEffectTitle: Assign the Effect to the Targets!

actions.hint: Some creatures are able to make more than one Standard action per round. A creature with multiple actions is able to attack multiple times, but certain types of attacks (and movement) are limited.
actions.label: Actions

standard.hint: The amount of normal damage the charater has taken.
standard.label: Lethal

stun.hint: The amount of stun damage the charater has taken.
stun.label: Stun

total.hint: The amount of normal damage and stun damage the charater has taken combined.
total.label: Total

death.hint: The Death Rating represents the the number of Damage Points needed to kill the character.
death.label: Death

unconscious.hint: The Unconsciousness Rating represents the number of Damage Points required to knock the character unconscious.
unconscious.label: Unconsciousness

woundThreshold.hint: Any attack that inflicts Damage Points at least equal to a characters Wound Threshold inflicts a Wound.
woundThreshold.label: Wound Threshold

wounds.hint: Each Wounds inflicts a -1 Step Penalty to tests, and a -1 to Recovery Test results.
wounds.label: Wounds

aggressiveAttack.hint: Gain a +3 bonus to close combat Attack and Damage tests, but suffer a 3 penalty to Physical and Mystic Defense for that round. Each attack costs 1 strain.
aggressiveAttack.label: Aggressive Attack

blindsided.hint: When a character cannot see an attacker, subtract 2 from Physical and Mystic Defense against the attack. This can also apply to Social Defense if appropriate
blindsided.label: Blindsided

full.hint: Full cover completely obscures a character, and they cannot be attacked without the use of special abilities or talents.
full.label: Full Cover

cover.hint: Characters can take advantage of cover as protection. Cover modifiers are applied against any attacks made against the character
cover.label: Cover

partial.hint: An attacker can still see enough of a target in cover to attack. Partial cover gives a +2 bonus to Physical and Mystic Defense.
partial.label: Partial Cover

full.hint: Full darkness is when there is almost no ambient light, and a lot of deep shadows. A character in full darkness suffers a 4 penalty to any sight-based tests.
full.label: Fulll Darkness

darkness.hint: If a character in darkness does not possess Heat Sight, Low-Light Vision, or a similar, their actions are impaired. Darkness modifiers are based on the amount of ambient light present.
darkness.label: Darkness

partial.hint: Partial darkness has some ambient light, but the environment is dark, with a lot of shadow. A character in partial darkness suffers a 2 penalty to any sight-based tests.
partial.label: Partial Darkness

defensiveStance.hint: The character adds +3 to his Physical and Mystic Defense for all attacks directed against them, that they are aware of, that round. The character suffers a 3 penalty to all tests that round, except for Knockdown tests.
defensiveStance.label: Defensive Stance

fury.hint: Instead of suffering penalties, Wounds grant a bonus to tests. Once the Wounds are greater than the Step of this ability, the bonuses are lost and the normal penalties for Wounds apply.
fury.label: Fury

harried.hint: A character being attacked in close combat by four or more opponents is considered harried, as are those affected by certain abilities. A harried character suffers a -2 penalty to tests, and Physical and Mystic Defense ratings. Opponents behind them benefit from the Blindside modifier.
harried.label: Harried

full.hint: Dense underbrush, a packed marketplace, full darkness, waist-deep water, and similar environments could reduce a characters Movement Rate by 10, or cause a -4 penalty to movement-based tests. In addition, characters might need to pass Dexterity tests to avoid tripping or having their movement halted (this test should not suffer the -4 penalty).
full.label: Heavily Impaired

impairedMovement.hint: At the gamemasters discretion, characters can suffer movement or test penalties depending on the environment.
impairedMovement.label: Impaired

partial.hint: Light brush, narrow alleyways, cramped rooms, partial darkness, and similar environments could reduce a characters Movement Rate by 5, or cause a -2 penalty to movement-based tests.
partial.label: Lightly Impaired

knockedDown.hint: A character who is knocked down can still act but is impaired. While prone characters suffer a 3 penalty to tests, and subtract 3 from Physical and Mystic Defense (this can apply to Social Defense). A Character can crawl at a Movement Rate of 2. These penalties remain in effect until the character stands up, which takes a Standard Action.
knockedDown.label: Knocked Down

overwhelmed.hint: Additional distractions disorient an already harried character. A harried character suffers a further 1 penalty to his tests and Defense ratings for each additional harried effect he incurs after the first.
overwhelmed.label: Overwhelmed

surprised.hint: Characters caught off guard may be surprised. Surprised characters cannot take any actions during the combat round in which they are surprised. They also suffer a 3 penalty to their Physical and Mystic Defense until the end of the Combat Round
surprised.label: Surprised

Dialogs.knockDownChoice: Chose the Ability to withstand the Knock Down

Warn.livingArmorOnly: This namegiver can only wear living armor.
Warn.piecemealArmorSizeExceeded: Maximum amount of piecemeal armor reached. Unequip other parts to equip the new piece.

Edid.languageSpeakHint: ED-ID for the Speak Language ability
Edid.spellCastingHint: Identifies a talent that is used for spellcasting
Edid.threadWeavingHint: Identifies a talent that is used for thread weaving

Hint.enforceLivingArmor: Enforce that only living armor can be equipped
